Program: Discovery
Title: On astronomy
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrz63
Last Broadcast Date: 30 May 2006
A discussion on astronomy with Professor Robert Kirshner of Harvard University. The former NASA astronaut Jeffrey Hoffman and MIT professor of aerospace engineering.presents a series of programmes. In the first he explains why having telescopes in space is helping our exploration of the heavens, the most famous being the Hubble Space Telescope. Show less